  "text": "The Envoy xDS v2/v3 API dual-version handling is implemented through a sophisticated template-based architecture in the gRPC subscription system. At the core is the unified xDS mux implementation in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h, which uses template parameters (RQ for request type, RS for response type) to support different protocol versions. The template is instantiated twice: GrpcMuxSotw (State-of-the-World) using envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest/Response, and GrpcMuxDelta using envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryRequest/Response.\n\nThe subscription state management is abstracted through BaseSubscriptionState<RS, RQ> template in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h, which handles the protocol state for individual xDS subscriptions. Two concrete implementations are provided: DeltaSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/cc) for delta xDS protocol and SotwSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/cc) for state-of-the-world protocol. Both handle the getNextRequestInternal() and handleGoodResponse() methods that construct v3 proto messages.\n\nThe v2-to-v3 field renaming and versioning is handled through protobuf annotations. The api/envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto file contains DiscoveryRequest, DiscoveryResponse, DeltaDiscoveryRequest, and DeltaDiscoveryResponse messages, each marked with udpa.annotations.versioning.previous_message_type pointing to their v2 counterparts (e.g., \"envoy.api.v2.DiscoveryRequest\"). This annotation system maintains backward compatibility through the protobuf migration infrastructure.\n\nThe ADS (Aggregated Discovery Service) gRPC server subscription handling integrates these components through the grpc_subscription_factory.cc file, specifically the AdsConfigSubscriptionFactory::create() method, which creates GrpcSubscriptionImpl instances that wrap the GrpcMux objects. The factory pattern in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.cc allows runtime selection between the legacy GrpcMuxImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h/cc) and the unified XdsMux::GrpcMuxSotw/GrpcMuxDelta implementations based on feature flags (envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux).\n\nType URL-based routing for different xDS APIs (CDS, EDS, LDS, RDS, etc.) is handled in source/common/config/type_to_endpoint.cc, which maintains mappings for v3 service endpoints including RouteDiscoveryService, ClusterDiscoveryService, EndpointDiscoveryService, ListenerDiscoveryService, and others. The type_url field in DiscoveryRequest/Response messages is used by the ADS server to multiplex multiple resource types over a single gRPC stream.\n\nThe dual-protocol architecture is achieved through the generic GrpcStream<RQ, RS> interface in the gRPC mux implementation, which allows the same subscription and stream management logic to handle both request and response message types transparently. Error handling and NACK/ACK mechanisms are implemented in subscription_state.h through the handleResponse() and handleBadResponse() methods that set error_detail fields in the request messages."
}

